[{"id":"VR615344","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block suspended between two vertical supports by means of two strings. String 1 is attached near the top of the left vertical support and extends down and to the right to connect to the top left corner of the block. String 2 is attached to the middle of the right vertical support and extends horizontally to the left to connect to the middle of the right side of the block.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR615344.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block of weight <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub g\"><math alttext=\"F sub g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>g</mi></msub></math></span></span> is suspended by two strings of negligible mass, as shown in the figure. The strings are also attached to vertical supports. The tensions in String <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and String <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> are <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, respectively. Which of the following correctly describes the magnitudes of the forces exerted on the block, and provides correct reasoning?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR615344_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> must be the largest because its horizontal component has a magnitude of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> and its vertical component has a magnitude of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub g\"><math alttext=\"F sub g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>g</mi></msub></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> must be the largest because the magnitude of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> must be less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub g\"><math alttext=\"F sub g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>g</mi></msub></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> must be the largest because it needs to provide an opposing force to both <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub g\"><math alttext=\"F sub g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>g</mi></msub></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> must be the largest because the magnitude of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> is less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"F sub g\"><math alttext=\"F sub g\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>g</mi></msub></math></span></span>.</p>"],"answer":0}]